		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">PID controller</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>A <b>proportional–integral–derivative controller</b> (<b>PID controller</b>) is a generic <a href="/wiki/Control_loop" title="Control loop" class="mw-redirect">control loop</a> <a href="/wiki/Feedback_mechanism" title="Feedback mechanism" class="mw-redirect">feedback mechanism</a> (<a href="/wiki/Controller_(control_theory)" title="Controller (control theory)">controller</a>) widely used in industrial <a href="/wiki/Control_system" title="Control system">control systems</a>. A PID controller attempts to correct the error between a measured <a href="/wiki/Process_variable" title="Process variable">process variable</a> and a desired <a href="/wiki/Setpoint_(control_system)" title="Setpoint (control system)">setpoint</a> by calculating and then outputting a corrective action that can adjust the process accordingly and rapidly, to keep the error minimal.</p>
